.  My agility is only 95.<br><br>For AC at lvl 60, 1200 is the unbuffed target.  That is the current hard deck for AC although I expect it to go up with Luclin.  At 1200 base AC your are taking the least amount of HP melee damage you can take given your personal Agility level.<br><br>That is the &quot;perfect&quot; level 60 cleric with good stats.<br><br>Below levlel 60 can be completely different.<br><br>From level 1-40 your primary need is wisdom and AC.  You need wisdom for casting your spells and AC to protect you from the consequences of using those spells.  Clerics are in the middle of the action - especially when you get group heals.  For the most part you can stand out of melee range.  As you level up, you find yourself closer and closer to the melee action requiring your AC to be sufficient. You should have 200 wisdom by the time you are lvl 30.  That can be a daunting task.  Lvl 35 would be as high as I would recommend without 200 wisdom. <br><br>From 40-50 you need to start trading in some of your standard gear/jewelry for resist producing stats.  That can be difficult until you get to the Planes at lvl 47.  Clerical Planes gear is actually not too bad through lvl 54.  By lvl 50 you really want every stat with some bonuses due to gear.  On my computer, stats with armor bonuses are green.  You want all your stats to be green then.<br><br>From lvl 50-54 you want to start upping the AC.  You have already boosted your stats some and have 200+ wisdom.  For the most part, you have sacrificed AC.  At 50+ you will be taking melee damage a lot.  You NEED AC.  However, trying to add AC without sacrificing your other stats is the trick.  PoG gear is not bad but I would hope you are beginning to get Velious items.  Small guilds lvl 50+ can easily hunt in Kael for very good armor with very good stats.  If your guild can take on Trak, hopefully you will get awarded the Donals BP.  It's a great BP and you really cant get anything much better unless you hunt in the Temple of Veeshan.  By 54 your unbiffed resists should be 60+ and your AC should be 900+.<br><br>From 55-60 your goal needs to be headed to the golas I mentioned in my first paragraphs.  100+ on all stats and 90+ on all resists.  It's tough to do that but very workable.  With good standard resists and good AC, you can take a lot of shit and still be there to heal your people.<br><br>This takes time but is definitely achievable.  Luclin will throw in new skills and abilities for clerics.  If we get most of what is rumored, clerics will be even more invaluable than they are now.  One example is the ability to res at 100% XP regain.  That makes death now more of just a time waster than an XP loser.<br><br>Chime in other clerics... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uraene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Battle Druid, Artist</span><br>  Posts: 443<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/01 2:30:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://ldnews.kyid.net/images/members/raene.jpg HEIGHT=160 WIDTH=140></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and over-all focus...</span><hr size=1> My cleric uses an Emerald Dragonscale BP, the bright green bp you often see mixed with purple gear<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eq.gameznet.com/equipment/ss/emeralddragonscaletunic.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>This is found in a quest given in Cobalt Scar by the Otters. While not as great as Donals, or PoG, or ToV/SS armor, is gives decent ac, great wisdom, and good MR. The dragon scale required for the quest drops off of Wuoshi. He dropped 3 when my guild killed him for traffic violations last week.<br><br>Wuoshi does fear, seems highly MR, but could be doable by public raids of appropriate tactics and level. His stun is PR based (mages...summon those shards!) Those wishing to keep good CoV faction will not want to take a faction hit, but might want to be available for CRs and rezz detail.  He also drops some nice ranger and druid loot, and spells. Rogues seem to like the Scimitar of Emerald Dawn for its stats, even when they have an epic in primary hand. I'm surprised this dragon doesn't die more often since he's a bio-hazard to those on Giant or Dorf faction. <br><br>Also good for MR is the Weight of the Gods from Plane of Sky<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eq.gameznet.com/equipment/ss/weightofgods.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>Hear about a public sky raid for a necro? Clerics go! :) Even at level 60 this remains (/knock on wood SoL) one of the best MR cleric pieces.<br><br><br><br><br><br> <p>Raene WolfRunner<br>60th Hierophant, Zebuxoruk<p>"Bother," said Pooh, "Eeyore, ready two photon torpedoes and lock phasers on the Heffalump. Piglet, meet me in transporter room three."<br>-----------------------------------------------------------------<p><center><TABLE border="1" bordercolor="#000000" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#000000"><TR><center>    <TD bgcolor="000000"><A href="http://2amstudios.com/eq/portraits.htm"><img src="http://www.2amstudios.com/eq/raene/plogo.jpg"  alt="Portraits by Raene" border="0"></A></TD>    <TD bgcolor="#000000">    <DIV align="center"><A href="http://www.kyid.net"><img src="http://ldnews.kyid.net/images/members/animesig/raenesig.gif"  alt="Lumiere Divine Guild" border="0"></A></DIV></tr></td><tr> <TD bgcolor="000000"><img src="ht